******************************
*****
*****  PERL PROGRAMMING  *****
*****
******************************

For those using Linux, there is a script named "setup-perl-linux.sh" which will
download various Perl programming language related documentation to your computer.
It will require Subversion (SVN), Git and Hg (Mercurial) to be installed.


Links:

https://www.perl.org/
https://www.perl.com/
https://www.cpan.org/
https://metacpan.org/
https://www.pm.org/
https://www.perlfoundation.org/
https://www.perlmonks.org/
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Perl_programming
https://rosettacode.org/wiki/Category:Perl
https://www.curlie.org/en/Computers/Programming/Languages/Perl/


